## What is a Large Language Model (LLM)?

A Large Language Model is a neural network trained on large amounts of text data.

LLMs work by predicting the next token (word or part of a word) based on previous tokens.

Example:

Input:
"Machine learning is"

Model prediction:
"powerful"
"important"
"a subset of AI"

Even though the training objective is simple, LLMs can perform complex tasks such as:
- question answering
- summarization
- translation
- coding
- reasoning


## ChatGPT vs API

ChatGPT:
- End-user interface
- Used directly through browser or app

API:
- Allows developers to access the model programmatically
- Used to build custom AI applications

Example use cases of API:
- chatbot
- document summarizer
- recommendation system
- AI assistant


